## Resolved mutable: mut-1780428153598

plugkit-wasm-wrapper.js gracefulCloseBrowser:1070-1075 kills entry.pid (the pid from spawn(browserBin) at :1008). On Windows, chrome launched with --user-data-dir relaunches itself as a detached process tree with a DIFFERENT pid; the recorded launcher pid exits immediately, so isProcessAliveSync(entry.pid)=false, the SIGTERM+killPidQuiet(entry.pid) no-ops on the dead launcher, and the REAL chrome (different pid, holding the profile + remote-debugging-port) survives untracked. Idle reaper (:2697) then deletes the ports entry regardless, so on resume getOrCreateBrowserSession sees empty ports -> aliveCdpForProfile rescan finds nothing (ports empty) -> startManagedBrowser spawns a SECOND chrome. User sees two browsers and must close both (the orphan is no longer in ports.json so nothing reaps it). Need: kill chrome by profileDir/port ownership (OS process query for --user-data-dir=<profileDir>), not just the recorded launcher pid.